---
description: how to verify C++ code changes
alwaysApply: false
---

- After modifying the C++ codebase, make sure to invoke the build on the current machine.
- This project utilizes the CMake and CMakePresets.json file. make sure to only invoke the build via the `cmake --preset` set of commands on either the entire project or the affected target.
so for instance if you added some files or modified CMake scripts, you should
1. invoke the relevant cmake preset to generate the build (`cmake --preset=<preset>`) 
2. invoke the relevant cmake preset on the affected target or the entire project (`cmake --build --preset=<preset> --target=<target>)
- Do not run cmake in non preset mode
